{"lemma":"أَشِعَّةٍ","slug":"أَشِعَّةٍ","root":"ش.ع.ع","root_slug":"ش-ع-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ع-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22413","n22414","n22415"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%90%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ray, beam","examples":[{"text":"وأوضح أن الجهاز الجديد، الذي يدعى «أكسبلورير»، يعطى^([sic]) أشعه^([sic]) صوتية حيث يقوم بعملية لمس عن بعد لأنه يقبس قوة النسيج عن طريق ذبذبات ميكانيكية دقيقة جدا بفضل الموجات التى^([sic]) تحدث قص^([sic]) داخل الجسم.","english":"He elucidated that the new device he calls “Explorer” gives sound waves where it undertakes a process of touching from afar for it derives the tissue strength by way of very subtle mechanical oscillations thanks to the waves which cause cutting inside the body."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"crossbar, spoke etc."},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَعَّ (šaʕʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃu.ʕaːʕ/","/ʃa.ʕaːʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22413","headword_ar":"شَعَاعٌ","root":"$E","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n. (see 1) used as an epithet, and therefore as masc. and fem. and sing. and pl.;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disordered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsettled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutafar~iqN","text_ar":"مُتَفَرِّقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aE~N","text_ar":"شَعٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [likewise an inf. n. used as an epithet,] applied [like the former] to anything, (K, TA,) such as blood, and an opinion, and a purpose, or an intention; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEiyEN","text_ar":"شَعِيعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is wrongly expl. in the K as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aE~N","text_ar":"شَعٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in another sense, as stated above; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEo$aAEN","text_ar":"شَعْشَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba damuhu $aEaAEFA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ دَمُهُ شَعَاعًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His blood went scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEaAEN","text_ar":"شَعَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to blood signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spirtling"},{"kind":"text","text":"from a wound made with a spear or the like; as in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafa*N","text_ar":"نَفَذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Az, TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEaAEN","text_ar":"شُعَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahabuwA $aEaAEFA","text_ar":"ذَهَبُوا شَعَاعًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They went away scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~apN $aEaAEN","text_ar":"اُمَّةٌ شَعَاعٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A nation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people, scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTaAyarati AlEaSaA $aEaAEFA","text_ar":"تَطَايَرَتِ العَصَا شَعَاعًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The staff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick, broke into scattered pieces;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as when one has broken it by striking with it upon a wall: and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaSabapu","text_ar":"القَصَبَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the reed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cane."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oYN $aEaAEN","text_ar":"رَاْىٌ شَعَاعٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A disordered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unsettled, opinion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosN $aEaAEN","text_ar":"نَفْسٌ شَعَاعٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mind of which the purposes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intentions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"himamuhaA","text_ar":"هِمَمُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the S [and O], for which, in the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humuwmuhaA","text_ar":"هُمُومُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously substituted, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the opinions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are disordered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsettled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it is not directed to a decided affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAra fuw^aAduhu $aEaAEFA","text_ar":"طَارَ فُوَادُهُ شَعَاعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His mind fled in a disordered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unsettled, state, as though dissipated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. as] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafar~aqato humuwmuhu","text_ar":"تَفَرَّقَتْ هُمُومُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a mistranscription, as before: correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tfr~qt himamuhu","text_ar":"تفرّقت هِمَمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his purposes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intentions, became disordered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsettled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see also Ham p. 44, and Har p. 366]. (K.) And a rájiz says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Algadaro ↓ \n      Sadoqu All~iqaA='i gayoru $aEo$aAEi"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Firm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"steady, in encounter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conflict,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not disordered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsettled, in respect of purpose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intention."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-  Hence, app., (TA,) Milk"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mixed with much water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, O;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DayaAHN","text_ar":"ضَيَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISh, O, K, TA.)       -A2-  Also [as a subst.] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"awn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the ears of corn; (S, O, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEaAEN","text_ar":"شُعَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEaAEN","text_ar":"شِعَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aE~N","text_ar":"شَعٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"awn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beard, when it has become dry, as long as it remains on the ears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEaAEN","text_ar":"شُعَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, O.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Z","S"]},{"entry_id":"n22414","headword_ar":"شَعَاعٌ","root":"$E","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uE~N","text_ar":"شُعٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, K) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rays,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beams,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the sun; or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what one sees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the light, like rods,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending like spears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the rising,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the beginning of the rising,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little after the rising,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,) of the sun; (S, O, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what one sees, like cords coming towards him, when looking at the sun;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersing light"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the sun: (K:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K) [and Freytag states that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEo$iEapN","text_ar":"شِعْشِعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said by Jac. Schultens to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rays:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this I do not find in any lexicon:] the pl. (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEaAEN","text_ar":"شُعَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", O) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$iE~apN","text_ar":"اَشِعَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) accord. to analogy, (O,) [a pl. of pauc.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEuEN","text_ar":"شُعُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEaAEN","text_ar":"شِعَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) the last anomalous. (TA.) Hence, in a trad. respecting [the night called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu Alqadori","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ القَدْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Al$~amosa taToluEu mino gadi yawomihaA","text_ar":"اـِنَّ الشَّمْسَ تَطْلُعُ مِنْ غَدِ يَوْمِهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA $uEaAEa lahaA","text_ar":"لَا شُعَاعَ لَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the sun will rise on its morrow having no rays"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S: in the O,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino gadihaA","text_ar":"مِنْ غَدِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  In the verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafa*N","text_ar":"نَفَذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", As is related to have read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uEaAEu","text_ar":"الشُّعَاعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aEaAEu","text_ar":"الشَّعَاعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brightness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and redness, and scattered state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the blood: ISd says, I know not whether he said it meaning by original application or by way of comparison. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEaAEN","text_ar":"شَعَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","AA"]},{"entry_id":"n22415","headword_ar":"شِعَاعٌ","root":"$E","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEaAEN","text_ar":"شَعَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence: ―         -b2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEaAEN","text_ar":"شُعَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}